"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DateFormatter in matplotlib is used to format the x-axis tick labels as dates. However, the DateFormatter is being used with a format string that does not match the format of the dates being plotted. The dates are being converted to a matplotlib date format using datestr2num, but the DateFormatter is being used with a format string that matches the original date format, not the converted format.\",\n  \"patch\": \"13c13\\n< ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%d/%m/%Y\\\"))\\n---\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%m/%d/%Y\\\"))\\n\"\n}"